Avegolemono
  --Cook's Illustrated

1 1/2	lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts, trimmed
Salt and pepper
12x3" strips lemon zest + 6 tbsp juice + extra juice for seasoning (3 lemons)
2	sprigs fresh dill + 2 tsp chopped
2	tsp coriander seeds
1	tsp black peppercorns
1	garlic clove, peeled and smashed
8	c chicken broth
1	c long-grain rice
2	large eggs + 2 large yolks

Cut each chicken breast in half lengthwise. Toss with 1 3/4 tsp salt and let stand at room temperature for at least 15 min or up to 30 min. Cut 8" square of triple-thickness cheesecloth. Place lemon zest, dill sprigs, coriander seeds, peppercorns, and garlic in center of cheesecloth and tie into bundle with kitchen twine. Bring broth, rice, and spice bundle to boil in large saucepan over high heat. Reduce heat to low, cover, and cook for 5 min. Turn off heat, add chicken, cover, and let stand for 15 min. Transfer chicken to large plate and discard spice bundle. Using two forks, shred chicken into bite-size pieces. Using ladle, transfer 1 c cooked rice to blender (leave any liquid in pot). Add lemon juice and eggs and yolks to blender and process until smooth, ~1 min. Return chicken and any accumulated juices to pot. Return soup to simmer over high heat. Remove pot from heat and stir in egg mixture until fully incorporated. Stir in chopped dill and season with salt, pepper, and extra lemon juice to taste. Serve.
